org.openbel.framework.ws.dialect
Class CustomDialect

java.lang.Object
  org.openbel.framework.ws.dialect.CustomDialect
All Implemented Interfaces:
Dialect
public class CustomDialect
extends Object
implements Dialect

Dialect implementation that allows control over the Namespace s used in conversion. An ordered list of Namespaces can be assigned to each of the NamespaceDomains; labeling for each Parameter in a supporting term will use these priorities to determine a String value. If a value cannot be found for a Parameter in the desired namespace, the next namespace in the list will be attempted. When all preferences are exhausted the label will default to the default label of the term.
This implementation also allows definition of the BELSyntax to be used and whether or not to strip the namespace prefixes from the returned labels.

Construction of this class is limited to DialectFactory#createCustomDialect(org.openbel.framework.core.kamstore.data.jdbc.KAMCatalogDao.KamInfo, List, List, List, BELSyntax, boolean)
This implementation caches labels for nodes and is thus suitable only for a single Kam. Usage across Kams is not guarded against but will cause unpredictable results.
This implementation is thread-safe.

Author:
Steve Ungerer
